    "Considerations": [
        "When a new printer driver is installed or an existing one is updated, it may modify registry keys under 'SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Monitors'. This legitimate activity can trigger a false positive alert.",
        "During routine system maintenance or Windows updates, registry keys related to print monitors may be modified. These changes are part of normal system operations and can result in false alerts.",
        "Certain third-party software, especially those related to printing or system monitoring, may modify the registry keys in question. These legitimate modifications can be mistaken for malicious activity, leading to false positives."
